\begin_layout Standard
The experiment measured the transversely polarized cross section difference
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta\sigma_{\bot}$
\end_inset

 in 5 settings with different beam energy and target magnet field.
 Combining with the longitudinal polarized cross section difference 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta\sigma_{\Vert}$
\end_inset

 from EG4 experiment, the 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{2}$
\end_inset

 is extracted as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
g_{2}=\frac{1}{K_{1}K_{2}}(\frac{\Delta\sigma_{\bot}}{K_{3}}-\frac{\Delta\sigma_{\Vert}}{K_{4}}),
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
K_{1} & =-\frac{4\alpha^{2}E'}{MQ^{2}E\nu},\nonumber \\
K_{2} & =\frac{2Mx}{E+E'cos\theta}+\frac{2E}{\nu},\nonumber \\
K_{3} & =E'sin\theta,\nonumber \\
K_{4} & =E+E'cos\theta,
\end{align}

\end_inset

The experiment also measured the 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta\sigma_{\Vert}$
\end_inset

 in one beam energy setting with 5 T target magnet field for checking the
 results from EG4 experiment.
 Detail run summary is in appendix.
\end_layout

